items.name: node-mail-server
items.description: A high-performance SMTP server built with  Node.js, TypeScript, and socket support, featuring DKIM, SPF, and comprehensive spam protection for secure email sending and receiving.

items.name: Expense-Tracker
items.description: An expense tracking application developed with Vue.js and Node.js. The app allows users to log expenses, categorize them, and visualize spending patterns. This project demonstrates modern web development techniques.

items.name: Blog-Platform
items.description: A blog platform built with Ruby on Rails. This project includes user authentication, post creation, and comment functionality, demonstrating proficiency in web development and Rails framework.

items.name: improving-transformers-world-model-for-rl
items.description: Implementation of the new SOTA for model based RL, from the paper "Improving Transformer World Models for Data-Efficient RL", in Pytorch

items.name: Recipe-Sharing-App
items.description: A recipe sharing application created with Angular and Firebase. Users can share their favorite recipes, leave reviews, and save recipes to their profile. This project showcases front-end development and cloud database integration.

items.name: Recipe-Book
items.description: A recipe book application developed with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Users can add, edit, and delete recipes, and filter them by category. This project is perfect for honing front-end development skills.

items.name: AITextGen
items.description: An experiment with natural language processing and text generation models.

items.name: TaskManager-App
items.description: A task management application built with React and Node.js. The app allows users to create, edit, and delete tasks. This project demonstrates full-stack development capabilities.

items.name: Currency-Converter
items.description: A currency converter application built with Java and JavaFX. The app fetches real-time exchange rates and converts currencies, demonstrating proficiency in desktop application development.

items.name: Chatbot-Application
items.description: A chatbot application built using Python and the Natural Language Toolkit (NLTK). This project demonstrates basic natural language processing (NLP) techniques and chatbot interactions.

items.name: Language-Learning-App
items.description: A language learning mobile application created with Swift. The app features vocabulary exercises, quizzes, and progress tracking. This project demonstrates mobile app development skills for iOS.

items.name: RustyUtils
items.description: A collection of handy Rust utilities for everyday programming tasks.

items.name: Data-Visualization-with-D3.js
items.description: A collection of data visualization examples using D3.js. This repository includes various charts and graphs to illustrate data insights and patterns.

items.name: Online-Quiz-Platform
items.description: An online quiz platform developed using PHP and MySQL. Users can create, take, and share quizzes, demonstrating back-end development and database management skills.
